This paper discusses the principles of weak cooperation and collective production in large social network communities, specifically on the photo publication website Flickr. It also includes statistics on the data basis collected from Flickr using the public API. Based on these topics, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Development), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
